item.title: Market slides as lockdown hurts confidence
item.description: Shares closed lower on Tuesday after a choppy trading day, with large-scale Victorian lockdowns overshadowing signals by the central bank of an economic recovery.

item.title: COVID-19 invades Melbourne hospital
item.description: A Melbourne hospital will temporarily divert some ambulances to other hospitals as a coronavirus outbreak in the facility’s emergency department grows.

item.title: AFP swoops on child abuse stash
item.description: Australian Federal Police have swooped on a man living in Sydney’s eastern suburbs who allegedly shared child abuse material with a minor.

item.title: Ex-Rabbitoh Doueihi was born to be a Tiger
item.description: Wests Tigers winger David Nofoaluma has lit the fuse for Friday’s clash against South Sydney after declaring that former Rabbitoh Adam Doueihi was destined to be a Tiger at NRL level.

item.title: Melbourne plunges back into lockdown
item.description: The whole city of Melbourne will be locked down in a desperate attempt to slow a surging rise of coronavirus infections.

item.title: Tigers hope Leilua learns lesson
item.description: Wests Tigers players expect a suspended Joey Leilua to return “twice the player” after a trademark Michael Maguire home truth prompted the emotional back to apologise to his teammates almost in tears.

item.title: Street drugs used to treat depression
item.description: Ketamine and nitrous oxide are being used to help treat depression in new clinical trials in Australia.

item.title: SA calls in army to keep Victorians out
item.description: South Australia will strengthen its southeastern border and implement stronger quarantine measures in a bid to protect the state from growing virus numbers in neighbouring Victoria.

item.title: Card payments surge as economy recovers
item.description: Latest monthly retail payment figures released by the Reserve Bank of Australia show a transaction bounce back across the economy.

item.title: Huge police and army presence at border
item.description: The start of a major police operation, which will include more than 650 police personnel, is now under way on the NSW-Victorian border ahead of a complete border closure at midnight.
